title: "Office building" (Premises), means a building or premises or part thereof whose sole or principal use is for an office or for office purposes
clause_text: "Office building" (Premises), means a building or premises or part thereof whose sole or principal use is for an office or for office purposes . "Office purposes" includes the purpose of administration, handling money, telephone, telegraph and computer operation and such other activities; and including writing, book-keeping, sorting papers, typing, filing, duplicating, data processing, drawing of matter for publication and editorial preparation of matter for publication and such other activities.
